{"_type":"issue","id":"tmpl-8z1.2","title":"fix _bd_dolt_push_smoke_test to use the real bd dolt push contract","description":"GREEN for tmpl-8z1 / scenario 62eb2a8b9b617f4b. Unblocks from RED (tmpl-8z1.1). In cli.py configure the Dolt remote (bd dolt remote add) using the rendered remote URL, run bare 'bd dolt push' (or --remote \u003cname\u003e), check the real exit code, exit bootstrap non-zero with a diagnostic on real failure.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"bc-implementer","owner":"dave@missingmass.io","created_at":"2026-06-18T17:01:37Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","updated_at":"2026-06-18T17:13:00Z","started_at":"2026-06-18T17:04:46Z","closed_at":"2026-06-18T17:13:00Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"tmpl-8z1.2","depends_on_id":"tmpl-8z1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-18T17:01:36Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","metadata":"{}"},{"issue_id":"tmpl-8z1.2","depends_on_id":"tmpl-8z1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-06-18T17:01:36Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":1,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"tmpl-8z1.1","title":"write the failing test asserting the REAL bd dolt push contract for the bootstrap smoke-test","description":"RED for tmpl-8z1 / scenario 62eb2a8b9b617f4b. Rewrite the conftest step + bd-shim so they assert the real bd contract: bootstrap configures a Dolt remote via 'bd dolt remote add \u003cname\u003e \u003curl\u003e' then runs bare 'bd dolt push' (no positional URL), checks the REAL exit code, and the shim REJECTS the old ['bd','dolt','push',\u003curl\u003e] positional shape. Must fail against the current no-op impl.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"bc-implementer","owner":"dave@missingmass.io","created_at":"2026-06-18T17:01:36Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","updated_at":"2026-06-18T17:04:45Z","started_at":"2026-06-18T17:03:41Z","closed_at":"2026-06-18T17:04:45Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"tmpl-8z1.1","depends_on_id":"tmpl-8z1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-18T17:01:36Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":1,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"tmpl-8z1","title":"bootstrap bd dolt push smoke-test (62eb2a8b9b617f4b) invokes a non-existent CLI shape and is a guaranteed no-op against real bd","description":"Reviewer (lead-wnps) BLOCK. _bd_dolt_push_smoke_test in src/shop_templates/cli.py invokes ['bd','dolt','push',remote] passing the rendered sync.remote URL as a positional argv token. Real 'bd dolt push' takes NO positional (Usage: bd dolt push [flags]; only --remote \u003cnamed-remote\u003e, which takes a remote NAME not a URL). Verified empirically: 'bd dolt push \u003curl\u003e' silently ignores the positional, pushes to the DEFAULT remote, and when none is configured prints 'No remote is configured - skipping' and EXITS 0. So the smoke-test always reports success and would NEVER catch a misconfigured/unreachable remote - defeating scenario 62eb2a8b9b617f4b's stated purpose. Compounding: behavior A writes a 'sync.remote' YAML key that bd does not read (bd uses 'bd dolt remote add \u003cname\u003e \u003curl\u003e' / Remotes section, not a sync.remote config key); bd's prefix key is 'issue-prefix' (hyphen) not the written 'issue_prefix'. Tests pass only because the bd-shim accepts any argv and the Then-step asserts the wrong contract (expected_remote in argv). Fix: implementer must invoke the real CLI - configure the Dolt remote (bd dolt remote add) and run 'bd dolt push' (or 'bd dolt push --remote \u003cname\u003e'), and rewrite the step to assert the real contract. Every other 'bd dolt push' usage in this repo (AGENTS.md, .beads/README.md, canonical bc.md/bc-router) uses bare 'bd dolt push'.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"dave@missingmass.io","created_at":"2026-06-18T16:56:37Z","created_by":"bc-implementer","updated_at":"2026-06-18T16:56:37Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
